content:
I went with `[^\)]*` for the rgb and hsl because it makes this regex about 100+ characters than other regex selectors for rgb and rgba. Plus this will work with sass colors. The `ig` flags passed are important for it to select all the hex values. If you don't pass the `i` flag you need to change `[a-f0-9]` to be `[a-fA-F0-9]`.

This would be like selecting it in a html attribute.
style="color: rgb(255,0,24)"
style="color: rgb(255, 0, 24)"
style="color: rgba(255, 0, 24, .5)"
style="color: hsla(170, 23%, 25%, 0.2 )"
style="color: #fff"
style="color: #f2ewq" this isn't a color
style="color: #F2F2F2"
style="color: 0x00ffff" This is a color with the `#` escaped

This shows how it would select the color in a css string
.foo{
 color: rgb(255,0,24);
 color: rgb(255, 0, 24);
 color: rgba(255, 0, 24, .5);
 color: hsla(170, 23%, 25%, 0.2 );
 color: #fff;
 color: rgba(#fff, .5) This shows it works with SASS
 color: #f2ewq; this isn't a color
 color: #F2F2F2;
 color: 0x00ffff; This is a color with the `#` escaped
}

This shows how it matches colors in a paragraph
Lorem ipsum rgb(255,0,24) sit amet, consectetur adipisicing rgb(255, 0, 24). Dolorum in quaerat ea numquam distinctio #F2F2F2 nulla magni consequatur fuga nam unde iure, minima velit impedit! Beatae, totam 0x00ffff nemo pariatur?
